The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: Foreign direct investment (FDI) fell 17.2 per cent to $7.01 billion in the first quarter of this fiscal. In 2009, India attracted FDI worth $36.6 billion, equivalent to 2.7 per cent of its gross domestic product, compared with Chinas $95- billion inflows, accounting for 1.9 per cent of its GDP. We are comfortable with the (FDI) inflow, whatever we are getting, officials said.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: K.S.R. Murthy, vice-president (component) of Hindustan Motors, the makers of the Ambassador car, has put in his paper today, industry sources said.                             
	 Calcutta, Sept. 1: The Life Insurance Corporation of India is targeting a first-premium income earning of Rs 6,575 crore from the eastern region. We require a growth rate of 25 per cent to achieve this target, LIC zonal manager R.R. Dash said here today.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 1: The government today appointed new chiefs for eight public sector banks, including Canara Bank, the Oriental Bank of Commerce and Uco Bank.                             
	 Mumbai, Sept. 1: Software exporter Tata Consultancy Services (TCS) today said its British subsidiary  Diligenta  had won two life and pension contracts worth 250 million.
                                                                                                                          
